{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01La1Q37M2faZH34VjCz8fd9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\n     2→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n     3→LANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22\n     4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram → AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration\n     5→ENTRY: src/index.js\n     6→TEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js\n     7→\n     8→MODULE_INDEX:\n     9→- src -> .prizm-docs/src/\n    10→- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n    11→- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n    12→- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm\n    13→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm\n    14→- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n    15→- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n    16→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n    17→- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n    18→- public -> (static web panel assets — no L1 doc)\n    19→\n    20→RULES:\n    21→- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() — never call executeAiCli directly for chat\n    22→- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}\n    23→- Safe-to-modify config keys: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n    24→- ANSI stripping happens in onAssistantChunk hook via ansiProcessChunk() — never strip in final reply path\n    25→- Web panel CSS z-index hierarchy: .app-header=10, command-dropdown=100, lightbox=200, toast=300; details in CLAUDE.md\n    26→- Web panel CSS modifier pattern: .status/.message/.output-box/.toast use modifier classes for state (connected/error/exit-error/success/info); dark mode overrides hardcoded light-palette values; details in CLAUDE.md\n    27→- Dark mode via @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) in styles.css; :root color-scheme is `light dark`; hardcoded #fff backgrounds overridden to var(--panel)\n    28→- CSS breakpoints: 900px collapses grids; 600px mobile layout (flex-wrap header, full-width buttons, reduced padding)\n    29→- Toast: showToast(msg, type) in public/js/main.js; type='success'|'error'|'info'; auto-dismisses 3s + 300ms fade-out animation\n    30→- Lightbox: openLightbox(src)/closeLightbox() in public/js/main.js; close on backdrop click (event.target !== img) or Esc keydown\n    31→- Spinner: setBusy(busy, text, activeBtn?) in public/js/main.js; adds .loading to activeBtn when busy; removes from all buttons when idle; .btn.loading uses ::before pseudo-element with color: transparent on button text\n    32→- Kbd hints: .kbd class (monospace, border-bottom-width:2px, rounded, --panel bg, --muted color) used inline next to buttons; wrapper divs .chat-form-actions/.exec-form-actions (flex, align-items:center) hold button+kbd pairs; .kbd uses only CSS vars so dark mode auto-switches without explicit override\n    33→- Empty state: .empty-state component (flex column, centered, CSS vars only) inside #chatMessages and .exec-result; updateChatEmptyState() checks .message.user/.message.assistant only (system msgs don't count); updateExecEmptyState(hasResult) toggles #execEmptyState and #execOutput wrapper; clearChatBtn must re-append #chatEmptyState after innerHTML='' before next appendMessage call\n    34→- Scroll button: #scrollToBottomBtn inside .chat-messages-wrapper (position:relative); .scroll-to-bottom uses opacity:0+pointer-events:none (hidden) vs .visible (shown); z-index:50; updateScrollToBottomBtn() on chatMessages scroll event; threshold 100px from bottom; uses only CSS vars (dark mode auto-switches)\n    35→- Copy button: each .output-box wrapped in .output-box-wrapper (position:relative); .copy-btn uses position:absolute top:6px right:6px; data-target attr holds output box ID; delegated document.click listener in main.js; copyToClipboard(el) checks trimmed text (empty or '-' → '内容为空' toast, else clipboard write → '已复制' toast); uses only CSS vars (dark mode auto-switches)\n    36→- Collapsible config panel: <details class=\"panel config-panel\" open>/<summary> native HTML collapse — no JS; open attr = default expanded; summary ::before ▶ rotates 90deg when [open]; uses only CSS vars (dark mode auto-switches without explicit override)\n    37→\n    38→UPDATED: 2026-03-23\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9677417f-767e-416d-8b53-da0e498b65dc","uuid":"c3f02133-7bc6-4c8b-801f-99e1c0aae250","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:46:03.344Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/root.prizm","content":"PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22\nDESCRIPTION: Telegram → AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration\nENTRY: src/index.js\nTEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src -> .prizm-docs/src/\n- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n- public -> (static web panel assets — no L1 doc)\n\nRULES:\n- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() — never call executeAiCli directly for chat\n- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}\n- Safe-to-modify config key