dcoded #fff backgrounds overridden to var(--panel)\n    28→- CSS breakpoints: 900px collapses grids; 600px mobile layout (flex-wrap header, full-width buttons, reduced padding)\n    29→- Toast: showToast(msg, type) in public/js/main.js; type='success'|'error'|'info'; auto-dismisses 3s + 300ms fade-out animation\n    30→- Lightbox: openLightbox(src)/closeLightbox() in public/js/main.js; close on backdrop click (event.target !== img) or Esc keydown\n    31→- Spinner: setBusy(busy, text, activeBtn?) in public/js/main.js; adds .loading to activeBtn when busy; removes from all buttons when idle; .btn.loading uses ::before pseudo-element with color: transparent on button text\n    32→- Kbd hints: .kbd class (monospace, border-bottom-width:2px, rounded, --panel bg, --muted color) used inline next to buttons; wrapper divs .chat-form-actions/.exec-form-actions (flex, align-items:center) hold button+kbd pairs; .kbd uses only CSS vars so dark mode auto-switches without explicit override\n    33→- Empty state: .empty-state component (flex column, centered, CSS vars only) inside #chatMessages and .exec-result; updateChatEmptyState() checks .message.user/.message.assistant only (system msgs don't count); updateExecEmptyState(hasResult) toggles #execEmptyState and #execOutput wrapper; clearChatBtn must re-append #chatEmptyState after innerHTML='' before next appendMessage call\n    34→- Scroll button: #scrollToBottomBtn inside .chat-messages-wrapper (position:relative); .scroll-to-bottom uses opacity:0+pointer-events:none (hidden) vs .visible (shown); z-index:50; updateScrollToBottomBtn() on chatMessages scroll event; threshold 100px from bottom; uses only CSS vars (dark mode auto-switches)\n    35→- Copy button: each .output-box wrapped in .output-box-wrapper (position:relative); .copy-btn uses position:absolute top:6px right:6px; data-target attr holds output box ID; delegated document.click listener in main.js; copyToClipboard(el) checks trimmed text (empty or '-' → '内容为空' toas